      "value": "<p>Although the portrait is identified by an inscription on the canvas as Mary of Modena (1658-1718), second wife of James II, this is clearly a misidentification. Rather, the sitter appears to resemble Frances Teresa Stuart, Duchess of Richmond (1647-1702), as a comparison for example with Lelyâ€™s portrait of the same sitter (Royal Collection Trust RCIN 404514) indicates. At some stage, the portrait, which was three-quarter length, has been extended on all sides to form a full-length portrait. The alteration was made possibly during the remodeling of the interiors at Doddington Hall by Sir John Delaval during the 1760s in order to enhance its presence.</p>"
